    a: "General Tech Services operates an EIAC accredited calibration laboratory in Sharjah with an Abu Dhabi office and a fleet of over 20 service vehicles — providing both on-site calibration services UAE at your facility and in-lab calibration services UAE at our Sharjah headquarters. Contact us at +971 6 5436933 or email mathews@generaltechuae.com for a consultation."
  },
  {
    q: "Does General Tech Services offer on-site calibration in UAE?",
    a: "Yes — General Tech Services offers on-site calibration services UAE across all seven Emirates — Dubai, Sharjah, Abu Dhabi, Ajman, Ras Al Khaimah, Fujairah, and Umm Al Quwain. Our fleet of over 20 service vehicles operates across the UAE — providing ISO 17025 traceable calibration at your facility to minimize operational downtime while maintaining full audit-ready documentation."
  },
  {
    q: "Where to buy Mitutoyo equipment in UAE?",
    a: "General Tech Services is the authorized Mitutoyo distributor UAE — supplying the complete Mitutoyo range of precision measurement instruments, CMMs, surface roughness testers, and calibration equipment to businesses across the UAE and GCC through our Sharjah headquarters and online shop at generaltechshop.ae with next day delivery available."
  },
  {
    q: "What calibration services does General Tech Services offer?",
    a: "General Tech Services provides ISO 17025 accredited calibration services UAE across 15 disciplines — Biomedical, Dimensional, Electrical, Flow, Force, Gas Analyser and Detector, Humidity, Mass, NDT, pH and Other Instruments, Pressure, Sound, Temperature, Torque, and Volumetric — serving businesses across every emirate and the GCC-wide."
  },
  {
    q: "Which calibration laboratory in UAE has the widest accreditation scope?",
    a: "General Tech Services holds one of the largest EIAC accreditation scopes in the UAE — covering 15 calibration disciplines. This makes General Tech Services the calibration laboratory with widest accreditation scope UAE businesses across every industry sector rely on for comprehensive single-source calibration compliance."
  },
  {
    q: "How to get a calibration certificate in UAE?",
    a: "Contact General Tech Services at +971 6 5436933 or visit our Sharjah laboratory. Our team will assess your instruments, perform ISO 17025 accredited calibration traceable to national and international standards, and issue a professionally documented calibration certificate recognized by UAE regulatory authorities and quality management auditors."
  },
  {
    q: "Which company offers ISO 17025 calibration in Sharjah?",
    a: "General Tech Services is the leading ISO 17025 calibration company in Sharjah — operating from our Sharjah headquarters since 1998 with full EIAC accreditation covering 15 calibration disciplines. As the most experienced professional calibration services UAE provider based in Sharjah, we serve businesses across all seven Emirates and the GCC with audit-ready, traceable calibration certificates."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does calibration cost in UAE?",
    a: "Calibration costs in UAE vary depending on the type of instrument, the number of instruments, the calibration discipline required, and whether on-site or in-lab service is needed. General Tech Services provides transparent, competitive pricing for all ISO 17025 certified calibration company UAE services. Contact us at +971 6 5436933 or email mathews@generaltechuae.com for a detailed quotation."
  }
];

const leftFaqs = faqs.slice(0, 5);
const rightFaqs = faqs.slice(5);
---

<section class="py-32 bg-white overflow-hidden" id="faq-section">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-12">
    
    <div class="flex flex-col items-center text-center mb-24 opacity-0 translate-y-8 reveal-faq">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-8">
        <div class="w-12 h-[2px] bg-[#FF0000]"></div>
        <span class="text-[12px] font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#FF0000]">Knowledge Base</span>
        <div class="w-12 h-[2px] bg-[#FF0000]"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-5xl lg:text-[72px] font-black tracking-tight text-general-black leading-[0.95] mb-8">
        Frequently Asked <br />
        <span class="text-[#FF0000] italic font-medium">Questions.</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="w-full max-w-xl mx-auto border-t border-gray-100 pt-6 mt-2">
        <p class="text-gray-500 font-light text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Essential information about General Tech Services UAE, ISO 17025 accreditation, and our industrial supply capabilities.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-x-16 xl:gap-x-24 border-t border-gray-200 relative">
      <div class="hidden lg:block absolute top-0 bottom-0 left-1/2 w-[1px] bg-gray-100 -translate-x-1/2"></div>

      {/* Left Column */}
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        {leftFaqs.map((faq, idx) => (
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200/80 faq-item">
            <button class="w-full py-8 flex items-start justify-between text-left group gap-6 outline-none transition-all duration-300 faq-trigger">
              <span class="text-[19px] lg:text-[21px] font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors duration-300 pr-4 leading-[1.3] text-general-black group-hover:text-[#FF0000]">
                {faq.q}
              </span>
              <div class="shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center transition-transform duration-500 mt-1 text-gray-300 group-hover:text-[#FF0000]">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="plus-icon"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="minus-icon hidden"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div class="overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 max-h-0 faq-content">
              <div class="pb-8 pr-8 text-gray-500 text-[16px] leading-relaxed font-light">
                {faq.a}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      {/* Right Column */}
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        {rightFaqs.map((faq, idx) => (
          <div class="border-b border-gray-200/80 faq-item">
            <button class="w-full py-8 flex items-start justify-between text-left group gap-6 outline-none transition-all duration-300 faq-trigger">
              <span class="text-[19px] lg:text-[21px] font-bold tracking-tight transition-colors duration-300 pr-4 leading-[1.3] text-general-black group-hover:text-[#FF0000]">
                {faq.q}
              </span>
              <div class="shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center transition-transform duration-500 mt-1 text-gray-300 group-hover:text-[#FF0000]">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="plus-icon"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="minus-icon hidden"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
              </div>
            </button>
            <div class="overflow-hidden transition-all duration-500 max-h-0 faq-content">
              <div class="pb-8 pr-8 text-gray-500 text-[16px] leading-relaxed font-light">
                {faq.a}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<script>
  const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');
  
  faqItems.forEach(item => {
    const trigger = item.querySelector('.faq-trigger');
    const content = item.querySelector('.faq-content');
    const plus = item.querySelector('.plus-icon');
    const minus = item.querySelector('.minus-icon');
    const text = item.querySelector('span');

    trigger?.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const isOpen = content.style.maxHeight !== '0px' && content.style.maxHeight !== '';
      
      // Close all others
      faqItems.forEach(otherItem => {
        if (otherItem !== item) {
          const otherContent = otherItem.querySelector('.faq-content');
          const otherPlus = otherItem.querySelector('.plus-icon');
          const otherMinus = otherItem.querySelector('.minus-icon');
          const otherText = otherItem.querySelector('span');
          const otherIconContainer = otherItem.querySelector('.faq-trigger div');
          
          otherContent.style.maxHeight = '0px';
          otherPlus?.classList.remove('hidden');
          otherMinus?.classList.add('hidden');
          otherText?.classList.remove('text-[#FF0000]');
          otherText?.classList.add('text-general-black');
          otherIconContainer?.classList.remove('text-[#FF0000]', 'rotate-180');
          otherIconContainer?.classList.add('text-gray-300');
        }
      });

      // Toggle current
      if (isOpen) {
        content.style.maxHeight = '0px';
        plus?.classList.remove('hidden');
        minus?.classList.add('hidden');
        text?.classList.remove('text-[#FF0000]');
        text?.classList.add('text-general-black');
        trigger.querySelector('div')?.classList.remove('text-[#FF0000]', 'rotate-180');
        trigger.querySelector('div')?.classList.add('text-gray-300');
      } else {
        content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + 'px';
        plus?.classList.add('hidden');
        minus?.classList.remove('hidden');
        text?.classList.add('text-[#FF0000]');
        text?.classList.remove('text-general-black');
        trigger.querySelector('div')?.classList.add('text-[#FF0000]', 'rotate-180');
        trigger.querySelector('div')?.classList.remove('text-gray-300');
      }
    });
  });

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.remove('opacity-0', 'translate-y-8');
        entry.target.classList.add('opacity-100', 'translate-y-0');
      }
    });
  }, { threshold: 0.1 });

  document.querySelectorAll('.reveal-faq').forEach(item => observer.observe(item));
</script>
